## [0.15.0] - 2023-08-11

### Added
- operators:
  - block-staircase: first version of this operator
  - holidays: autotrophic operator for holidays
  - round: round operator (migrated decimals option from trig)
  - abs: absolute value operator
  - sub: subtraction operator with migration for * -1 formulas
  - by.basket: filter using pre-defined basket name
- operators/findseries:
  - fill option implementation
  - #:naive keyword (searches tzaware by default)
  - allow filters yielding no series
- tsio:
  - expanded: allow specifying expansion depth (levels)
  - depth: compute formula depth (max traversal to bottom)
- api:
  - formula_depth: expose method to get formula depth
  - formula: level parameter to expand to desired depth
  - update_metadata: new api point (replace_metadata renamed)
- search: 
  - filter by formula contents
  - filter to separate formulas from primaries
  - namespace parameter to sql method
- migrate: switch to automatic migration system
- build: tox and ruff configuration
- pkg: tshclass and httpclient entry points
- __version__ attribute in package root

### Changed
- groups: schema unification (everything into group_registry, metadata split)
- operators: prepare retirement of findnames and serieslist (findseries does all)
- types:
  - function_types: use List[...] annotation for varargs
  - typename: do not undecorate List types
  - use Packed rather than List to indicate varargs
- tshistory/update_metadata: renamed to replace_metadata
- tsio/metadata: initial metadata must be empty dict
- operators/slice: simplify implementation and docstring
- conftest: specialize test machinery for formula specific routes
- http/formula: return asked level of expansion
- doc/readme: remove obsolete infos

### Fixed
- test/slice_vs_tzaware: fixed by tshistory package update
- test/empty_filter: prepare for allowing formulas on initially empty filters
- test/operator: align with tshistory/find alignment
- test/http: repair bound formula group tests
- operators/holidays: silence deprecation warning
- operators/round: migrate decimals option from trig
- api/formula-components: fix typo in docstring
- tsio: various name errors and cleanups
- helper/depth: avoid crasher in obscure corner case
- migrate: remove refs to supervision_status

### Removed
- operators: retire findnames and serieslist (replaced by findseries)

## [0.14.0] - 2023-02-24

### Added
- operators:
  - serieslist, findnames: get series lists using find api
  - findseries: combo of serieslist + findnames
  - comparators: <, <=, >, >=, <>, == (compare series to scalar or series)
  - complete set of filters and logical search operators
- patch: patch formula values (more basic than supervision)
  - complete rename and delete methods
  - verify behavior with patched NaNs
- psyl SPLICE operator (<|) support for tuple unpacking
- tsio: tz-aware checker for dynamic series (by filters)
- cli:
  - migrate-formula-schema: schema changes for metadata and tables reorg
  - patch: migration command

### Changed
- schema: unify formula registry with tshistory stored series registry
  - internal metadata carries all needed information
  - search and filters work on unified table and structure
- tsio/internal_metadata: follow tshistory split of internal vs user metadata
- group/metadata: fix after series metadata work completed
- rename: dependant -> dependent throughout
- interpreter: automatic list unpacking (SPLICE no longer needed)
- operators: doc fixes, enhancements, missing docstrings
- types: extract typing helpers to dedicated module
- operators/add: do not crash when no series (can happen with serieslist)
- operators/trig: better round operation (clearer code)
- operators/comparator: specify dtype for future compatibility
- tsio/check_tz_compat: complete integration of tz aware checks

### Fixed
- helper/expanded: remove bogus defensive condition
- type fixes noted through pytype
- test/formula: use vendored decorator lib

### Removed
- cli: retire unused command line tools

## [0.13.1] - 2023-02-24

### Fixed
