## [0.11.0] - 2022-06-23

### Added
- scope mechanism for operators to restrict query boundaries
  - @argscope decorator for operators
  - series operator uses scoped parameters (__from_value_date__, __to_value_date__, __revision_date__)
  - naive, time-shifted operators define scopes
- operators:
  - asof: get subexpression series in different revision
  - options/limit: better fillna tunability
- groups:
  - group_insertion_dates: support for group formulas with bounds
  - group_history: low level api point with from/to bounds
  - support for hijacked formulas
- tsio:
  - dependants: store and compute reverse dependencies between formulas
  - live_content_hash: compute content-hash on the fly
  - iter_revisions: internal api point for memory-efficient iteration
- api:
  - eval_formula: evaluate formulas on-the-fly before registration
  - formula: display parameter to inhibit macro-expansion
  - insertion_dates: accept from/to_value_dates
- cli:
  - rename-operators: handle group formulas
  - migrate-to-content-hash: faster implementation
  - migrate-to-dependants: handle dependencies between formulas
- schema: keep hash of expanded formula (content-addressable)
- evaluator: configure concurrency level
- license text added

### Changed
- operators:
  - rename min/max to row-min/row-max (prepare for scalar min/max)
  - rename timedelta to shifted
  - rename shift to time-shifted
  - series: remove dependency on interpreter.getargs
  - constant: use scoped query parameters, ensure index not shifted
  - naive: more robust with tz-aware bounds
- evaluator:
  - dispatch threaded/sequential based on concurrency level
  - replace complex quasiexpreval with lighter resolve function
  - cache result of funcid (performance)
- tsio:
  - history: major refactoring for clarity
    - extract autotrophic operator history computation
    - extract gap filling logic
    - extract diff computation
    - better naming throughout
  - insertion_dates: tidy parameter passing
  - expanded: inject top-level query arguments as variable bindings
- interpreter:
  - history: immediately stuff getargs with revision date
  - groups: simplify implementation
- registry:
  - history: require __interpreter__ for auto operators
  - remove update parameter from register_formula
- editor: fix behavior with empty series (remove buggy conditional)
- http: use provided session (important for security context)

### Fixed
- operator/slice: use tzaware_series predicate
- evaluator: fix pool parameter in non-threaded path
- operator/constant: should not adopt shifts of outer query parameter
- operators/clip: transfer options through operator
- operators/min-max: fix docstring
- operators/asof: working implementation for history
- tsio/log: return empty list on formulas
- funcs/scope: fix crash with embedded naive in slice
- repair name builder for autotrophic operators history

### Removed
- operators/series: retire prune option (replaced by slice)
- operators: retire tuple operator

