## [0.8.0] - 2020-12-11

### Added
- operators:
  - rolling: base support for rolling operations
  - tuple: provide tuple operator (enables multiple aggregation operators)
  - start-of-month: yield start of month for provided date
  - end-of-month: yield end of month for provided date
  - constant: constant series generator with full api support (history, insertion_dates)
- insertion_dates protocol for autotrophic operators
  - efficient implementations with from/to parameters
  - avoids double parse
- registry/auto: new protocol to distinguish ordinary from autotrophic operators
- evaluator: thread-pool based concurrency (replaces thread-spawning)

### Changed
- func/arith: provide better argument names for tsview/formula editor
- operators/today: 
  - move implementation to interpreter (special operator)
  - time-travel support (bound to revision_date)
  - works with history api point
- operators/naive: more index deduplication in naive path
- evaluator: 
  - evaluate formula on expansion to avoid deadlocks
  - use auto registry for thread execution decisions
  - pass trees instead of formula strings (less overhead)
- helper/expanded: 
  - do not lose track of expanded series options
  - only expand on series operator
- autotrophic formulae: use expression tree as key (not values) for time-travelling today

### Fixed
- tsio/update: raise ValueError on attempts to update formula (prevents hidden primary)
- funcs: repair _grouping series when one has no value in requested bounds
- operators/groups: fix behavior with fill option and bounds out of data
- operators/constant: handle time-travelling today errors with naive revision dates
- use empty_series helper to build correct empty series (naive or tzaware)

### Removed
- cli: remove dead code
- registry: remove unused leftover

## [0.7.3] - 2020-08-17

### Fixed
