## [0.7.0] - 2020-07-02

### Added
- operators:
  - cumsum: expose pandas series cumsum
  - shift: shift forward index dates (using timedelta for performance)
  - clip: keywords #:replacemin #:replacemax to fill out-of-bounds with boundaries
  - min,max,std,mean: supply #:skipna option
- api:
  - formula_components: expose find_series protocol, support expanded series and alt sources
  - insertion_dates: handle all components including remote ones, support autotrophic operators
- registry: add metadata protocol (separate from finder protocol)
- types: introduce Default term to handle default values
- interpreter/history: provide convenience callback for autotrophic operators
- cli:
  - migrate: command to fix bad metadata (remove supervision_status)
  - shell: use timeseries api object (accepts https uris)

### Changed
- operators/date: remove naive param, impose default UTC for tz parameter
- operators/resample: do not produce NaNs
- operators/naive: 
  - handle duplicates on DST switch using groupby->mean
  - do not crash on empty series or when applied to naive series
- operators/priority: 
  - use patchmany for performance (6.6s to 0.9s)
  - do not start from empty series
  - support single series input
- operators/slice: 
  - do not attempt to slice empty series
  - drop tzinfo over tznaive series
  - handle out-of-bounds slicing
- operators/min,max,row-mean: drop NaNs at the end
- operators/mul,div: handle no data situation
- tsio: overhaul series compatibility check (focus on tzawareness)
- tsio/register-formula: 
  - ensure top-level expression is a series
  - drop compat_excluded items from metadata
- types: switch from getfullargspec to signature objects
- api/formula_components: crack the wall of opaque formulas, provide dependencies tree

### Fixed
- register-formula: forbid registration over existing primary series (TypeError)
- operators/today: fix naive optionality
- operators/clip: fix replacemin usage
- tsio/update_metadata: fix entry removal
- tsio/history: fix serious issue with custom operator history
- interpreter: history lookup for autotrophic series more lenient
- group_series: do not crash on empty series
- naive: on empty series, do not reuse empty tz-aware index
- api: fix crash on some autotrophic operators for idates

### Removed
- migration: remove slice rewriter
- cli: remove old migration command

## [0.6.0] - 2020-02-04

