## [0.4.0] - 2019-10-28

### Added
- operators:
  - `/`: division operator (separate from div)
  - row-mean: weighted row-mean over variable number of series
  - row-min: row minimum across series
  - row-max: row maximum across series
  - std: standard deviation operator (removes NaN when N<2)
  - naive: operator to drop timezone info with target timezone
- api:
  - expanded_formula: recursively substitute formulas within formulas
- typechecker: complete type checking system for formulas
  - type checking at registration time
  - normalize types (Optional vs Union)
  - better error messages for missing return types
- cli:
  - update-metadata: add --reset option
  - complete migration from aliases (rewrite outliers to clip)
  - safety belt for alias tables drop
  - typecheck-formula: command to type check all formulas
- helper: constant-folding rewriter for basic arithmetic
- documentation:
  - operators documentation in docstrings
  - document naive operator
  - notes on literals syntax
  - operators ordered lexicographically

### Changed
- slice: preserve input series options
- metadata: propagate all metadata (fixes tshistory_client formula fetch)
- operators: +/* only take series as second argument, allow pure scalar arguments
- finder: use protocol for series operator
- editor: 
  - support new operators out of the box
  - fix handling of complex subexpressions
  - use constant folding for meaningful display
- register_formula: store normalized formula
- test: move editor tests to own module

### Fixed
- editor: fix regression
- std: remove NaN from results when N<2
- types: fix many typing errors discovered by typechecker

### Removed
- completely retire tshistory_alias

## [0.3.0] - 2019-09-18

### Added
- operators:
  - slice: slice operator for series subsetting
  - mul: multiplication operator
  - div: division operator
  - clip: better name for outliers operator
- documentation:
  - comprehensive operator documentation (slice, clip, add, priority, mul, div, *, /)
  - better introduction section
  - improved api section
  - documentation on operator implementation

### Changed
- tsio: extract formula evaluation method to get value by formula (not just by name)
- funcs: ensure all series-returning functions have an `options` attribute

## [0.2.0] - 2019-09-05

### Added
- delete: implement formula deletion
- metadata: compute internal metadata from formula constituents
- metadata: allow specifying metadata for custom operators
- staircase: add fast path optimization for safe formulas
- cli: fix migration command

### Changed
- series: make pruning a general option (not just for priority)
- funcs: use "fill" as internal fill option name for clarity
- funcs: use accessor to get options (better third-party operator support)
- find_series: walks the whole tree properly
- register_formula: report unknown operators and refuse to register

### Fixed
- metadata/update: fix name error
- rename: properly rename the formula when requested
- update_metadata: fix super call
- find_series: ensure complete tree traversal

### Removed
- caches: dropped following tshistory changes
- tsio: removed delta after/before following tshistory

## [0.1.0] - 2019-07-15

### Added
- initial working formula and base infrastructure
- operators:
  - series: fetch time series by name
  - add/+: linear series combinations (addition)
  - priority: build series from several by successive patch application
  - outliers: outliers handling function
  - mul/*: scalar × series product
  - naive: timezone handling
- formula registration with validation:
  - detect malformed formulas
  - detect non-existent series references
  - detect unknown operators
- api methods:
  - register_formula: register new formulas
  - get_formula: retrieve formula definition
  - type: get series type
  - exists: check series existence
  - get_history: retrieve formula history
  - list_series: list available series
  - rename: rename series and update formula references
  - metadata: metadata support
- interpreter: lisp-like formula evaluation engine
- staircase computation with optimizations
- cli commands:
  - convert-aliases: convert from legacy alias system
  - compare-aliases: compare alias vs formula results
  - ingest: load formulas from csv file
  - shell: interactive shell with formula features
- editor helper for formula information collection
- schema: formula table in dedicated namespace
- fill option: accept plain values
- pass get parameters down to individual series
- conversion from legacy alias component

### Changed
- interpreter: separate normal from history interpreter
- prio/arith: use *args notation instead of wrapping in list
- schema: ensure formula names are unique

### Fixed
- staircase/gethistory: handle None values properly
- interpreter/history: ensure series object has proper name
- interpreter/get: produce empty series when no data
- register: fix parameter typo
- convert/aliases: fix conversion for options, allow multiple runs